description.narrative:
Overall objective: 
Improved health and learning performance of school-aged children especially girls and their communities by reducing the incidence of water and sanitation-related diseases.  
Specific objectives are: 
•	Improved primary school attendance, health and cognitive development of a child through which WASH may affect early child development, primarily through inflammation, stunting, and anemia;
•	Greater girls’ participation in school;
•	Positive hygiene behaviours that may last for life which will helps children develop essential life skills that enable them to take greater responsibility of their own lives based on education that will essentially centre hygiene practices in children’s daily reality, while helping children acquire both knowledge of appropriate hygiene behaviours and the skills to use them;
•	Outreach to families and communities, through the participation of students in hygiene promotion
•	Greater equity in schools in the use and access of WASH facilities.
